
[1]stile

   STILE, n. [This is another spelling of style. See Style and Still.] A
   pin set on the face of a dial to form a shadow.

   Erect the stile perpendicularly over the substilar line, so as to make
   an angle with the dial-plane equal to the elevation of the pole of your
   place.

     STILE, n. [G. See Stair.] A step or set of steps for ascending and
                   descending, in passing a fence or wall.
